Anode Connection: In your previous code, you tried to connect anode => an inside the port map. Since an is 8 bits and anode is 4 bits, the synthesis tool would have failed or behaved unpredictably. Now, s_an_4 carries the signal from the driver, and we manually assign it to the lower half of the 8-bit bus.

Display Blanking: an(7 downto 4) <= "1111"; solves your problem of all 8 segments being on. This forces the transistors for the left 4 digits to stay closed.

Port Mapping Consistency: Made sure all signal names match between the component declarations and the port map.

