The error is happening for the same reason as before: your Testbench is still using the "old" interface for the display driver.

Since we added sw_in to the display_driver entity to allow for the Live Preview feature, the testbench now must provide a signal for that port. If you don't connect anything to it in the port map, the simulator doesn't know what to do with that input and throws the "no actual value" error.

Here is the corrected testbench. I've added a new signal s_sw_in and connected it so you can also simulate the preview feature!

