library ieee;
use ieee.std_logic_1164.all;

entity tb_display_driver is
end tb_display_driver;

architecture test of tb_display_driver is
    signal s_clk     : std_logic := '0';
    signal s_rst     : std_logic;
    signal s_data_in : std_logic_vector(15 downto 0) := (others => '0');
    signal s_sw_in   : std_logic_vector(3 downto 0)  := (others => '0'); -- ADDED THIS
    signal s_idx_pos : std_logic_vector(1 downto 0)  := "00";
    signal s_seg     : std_logic_vector(6 downto 0);
    signal s_anode   : std_logic_vector(3 downto 0);
    signal s_dp      : std_logic;

    constant CLK_PERIOD : time := 10 ns;

begin
    uut: entity work.display_driver
        port map (
            clk      => s_clk,
            rst      => s_rst,
            data_in  => s_data_in,
            sw_in    => s_sw_in,   -- ADDED THIS CONNECTION
            seg      => s_seg,
            anode    => s_anode,
            idx_pos  => s_idx_pos,
            dp       => s_dp
        );

    s_clk <= not s_clk after CLK_PERIOD / 2;

    stim_proc: process
    begin
        -- Reset phase
        s_rst <= '1';
        wait for 100 ns;
        s_rst <= '0';
        wait for 100 ns;

        -- Test Case 1: Displaying saved data
        s_data_in <= x"1234";
        s_idx_pos <= "01";      -- Cursor on second digit
        s_sw_in   <= x"F";      -- Live preview should show 'F' on second digit
        wait for 1 us;        

        -- Test Case 2: Change live preview
        s_sw_in   <= x"A";      -- Now preview should show 'A'
        wait for 1 us;

        -- Test Case 3: Move cursor and data
        s_data_in <= x"A55A";
        s_idx_pos <= "11";      -- Cursor on fourth digit
        s_sw_in   <= x"3";      -- Preview '3' on fourth digit
        
        wait for 1 us;

        wait; -- End of simulation
    end process;
end test;
What was changed?
Signal Declaration: Added signal s_sw_in : std_logic_vector(3 downto 0); so we have a "wire" to plug into the new port.

Port Map: Included sw_in => s_sw_in in the uut instantiation. This satisfies the compiler's requirement that every input port must have a value.

Stimulus: I added some lines in the stim_proc to change s_sw_in. When you run the simulation, you should see that the seg output changes whenever s_sw_in changes (for the digit selected by s_idx_pos).

One Quick Tip for Simulation: In your display_driver.vhd, you probably have G_MAX => 100_000. In a simulation, waiting for 100,000 clock cycles takes a long time! For the testbench to run fast, you can temporarily change that G_MAX to 10 just to see the digits switching in the waveform.

Just remember to change it back to 100,000 before you generate the bitstream for the Nexys board!

